'''Joe Bodolai''' was a Canadian comedian, television and film writer and producer.

Bodolai is best known for producing and writing such television shows as ''[[It's Only Rock & Roll (TV series)|It's Only Rock & Roll]]'', ''[[Comics!]]'', ''[[The Kids in the Hall]]'' and ''[[Saturday Night Live]]''.  He also co-wrote the first draft of the film ''[[Wayne's World]]'' with [[Mike Myers]].

Bodolai was found dead on December 26, 2012 in a Hollywood hotel room of an apparent suicide by consuming a mixture of Gatorade and anti-freeze.  He was 63.<ref>[http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/lanow/2011/12/former-snl-writer-joe-bodolai-dead-of-apparent-suicideicide.html The Los Angeles Times]</ref><ref>[http://www.tmz.com/2011/12/27/joe-bodolai-saturday-night-live-dead-dies-suicide/ TMZ]</ref><ref>[http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/saturday-night-live-writer-joe-bodolai-suicide-276390 The Hollywood Reporter]</ref><ref>[http://online.wsj.com/article/APab0d3a17d8d04299b8c65b72c2a0e2f2.html The Wall Street Journal]</ref>

